JS is a single threaded synchronuos language
Event loop has a behavious of non blocking, asynchronous despite being single threaded.
This allows JS to run I/O operations, timers, vents etc


Call Stack: Where function calls are executed (LIFO - Last In, First Out)

Web APIs: Browser-provided APIs (setTimeout, DOM events, HTTP requests)

Callback Queue (Task Queue): Holds callbacks waiting to be executed

Microtask Queue: For promises and mutation observers (higher priority)

Event Loop: The coordinator that manages everything


JS has a runtime nvironment


Nodejs is a open source JS run time environment
Nodejs can run js outside browser with libuv

In terms of node libuv library is used to manage I/O operations.